<h2 id="how">How does this work?</h2>

<p>Assuming a standard root font size of <code>16px</code> (thatâ€™s the <code><html></code> element in most cases):</p>

<pre><code id="result">X = (fontSizeMax - fontSizeMin) / (viewportWidthMax - viewportWidthMin)
X = (18px - 16px) / (1000px - 500px)
X = 0.004

A = fontSizeMax - viewportWidthMax * X
A = 18px - 1000px * 0.004
A = 14px = 0.875rem

B = X * 100vw
B = 0.004 * 100vw
B = 0.4vw

Result = clamp(fontSizeMin, A + B, fontSizeMax)
Result = clamp(1rem, 0.875rem + 0.4vw, 1.125rem)</code></pre>

